  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>Lady of\n        the Rocks</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p>The title \"Lady of the Rocks\" suggests\n        Madonna (the Virgin Mary) and, therefore, the Madonna of\n        the Rocks, as in Leonardo da Vinci's painting; the rocks\n        symbolize the church (see note above). </p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font>The Rock</font></td>\n<td><a href=\"publication_data.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>link two</td>\n<td><a href=\"title_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Waste_A.htm\"><font>back to \"The Waste Land\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Lady of the Rocks The title \"Lady of the Rocks\" suggests Madonna (the Virgin Mary) and, therefore, the Madonna of the Rocks, as in Leonardo da Vinci's painting; the rocks symbolize the church (see note above). reference topics The Rock link two back to \"The Waste Land\"",
